  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "54ba32d4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Creating timeseries illustating alternate equivalence rules"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "14a1989e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The relationship we've currently captured in `project-fluxes` and `justified_emission_fluxes` is based on GWP 100 logic. How would the world be different if a different accounting rule had been implemented? \n",
    "\n",
    "We're going to play with the following equivalency metrics, assuming the quantity of project gases are held equal. \n",
    "- GWP20: weights gases by their cumulative radiative forcing effect over 20 years\n",
    "- GWP100: weights gases by their cumulative radiative forcing effect over 100 years (redoing this using the latest GWP values for direct comparability)\n",
    "- GTP50: weights gases by their temperature impact at year 50\n",
    "- GTP100: weights gases by their temperature impact at year 100.\n",
    "\n",
    "We're also going to explore a like-for-like framework. Given the projects that occurred, and the emissions that could be justified, what would the offsetting outcome look like if gases had to be matched by atmospheric lifetime? In this case, we'll have a long-lived bucket (i.e. allow N2O and CO2 emissions to be matched with CO2 or CFC-12 project fluxes, given they all have lifetimes >100 years) and a short-lived bucket (i.e. CH4 project fluxes may only justify CH4 emissions, and any surplus CH4 mitigation beyond available CH4 emissions is dropped from the offsetting program)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "id": "e1968c94",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Values from AR6, Ch7 supplementary material, Table 7.SM.6\n",
    "# https://www.ipcc.ch/report/ar6/wg1/downloads/report/IPCC_AR6_WGI_Chapter07_SM.pdf\n",
    "\n",
    "gwp_20 = {\n",
    "    'ch4':   81.2,\n",
    "    'n2o':   273,\n",
    "    'cfc-12': 11400,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "gwp_100 = {\n",
    "    'ch4':   27.9,\n",
    "    'n2o':   273,\n",
    "    'cfc-12': 11200,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "gtp_50 = {\n",
    "    'ch4':   11,\n",
    "    'n2o':   290,\n",
    "    'cfc-12': 11800,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "gtp_100 = {\n",
    "    'ch4':   5.38,\n",
    "    'n2o':   233,\n",
    "    'cfc-12': 9270,\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 65,
   "id": "ad225171",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "                CO2           CH4        CFC-12         total\n",
      "GWP20   128982213.0  5.206148e+07  1.727971e+07  1.983234e+08\n",
      "GWP100  128982213.0  1.788812e+07  1.697656e+07  1.638469e+08\n",
      "GTP50   128982213.0  7.052663e+06  1.788602e+07  1.539209e+08\n",
      "GTP100  128982213.0  3.449393e+06  1.405113e+07  1.464827e+08\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# recalculate the number of credits generated using different equivalency metrics \n",
    "# CO2 stays exactly the same across the metrics and CFC-12 is similar; CH4 varies a lot\n",
    "\n",
    "def calc_credits(df, ch4_gwp, cfc12_gwp):\n",
    "    return (\n",
    "        df['co2_flux'].abs() +\n",
    "        df['ch4_flux'].abs() * ch4_gwp +\n",
    "        df['cfc-12_flux'].abs() * cfc12_gwp\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "pf = project_fluxes[project_fluxes['year'] <= 2025].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "pf['credits_gwp20']  = calc_credits(pf, gwp_20['ch4'],  gwp_20['cfc-12'])\n",
    "pf['credits_gwp100'] = calc_credits(pf, gwp_100['ch4'], gwp_100['cfc-12'])\n",
    "pf['credits_gtp50']  = calc_credits(pf, gtp_50['ch4'],  gtp_50['cfc-12'])\n",
    "pf['credits_gtp100'] = calc_credits(pf, gtp_100['ch4'], gtp_100['cfc-12'])\n",
    "\n",
    "gas_totals = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'GWP20':  {\n",
    "        'CO2':   pf['co2_flux'].abs().sum(),\n",
    "        'CH4':   pf['ch4_flux'].abs().sum() * gwp_20['ch4'],\n",
    "        'CFC-12': pf['cfc-12_flux'].abs().sum() * gwp_20['cfc-12'],\n",
    "        'total': pf['credits_gwp20'].sum()\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    'GWP100': {\n",
    "        'CO2':   pf['co2_flux'].abs().sum(),\n",
    "        'CH4':   pf['ch4_flux'].abs().sum() * gwp_100['ch4'],\n",
    "        'CFC-12': pf['cfc-12_flux'].abs().sum() * gwp_100['cfc-12'],\n",
    "        'total': pf['credits_gwp100'].sum()\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    'GTP50': {\n",
    "        'CO2':   pf['co2_flux'].abs().sum(),\n",
    "        'CH4':   pf['ch4_flux'].abs().sum() * gtp_50['ch4'],\n",
    "        'CFC-12': pf['cfc-12_flux'].abs().sum() * gtp_50['cfc-12'],\n",
    "        'total': pf['credits_gtp50'].sum()\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    'GTP100': {\n",
    "        'CO2':   pf['co2_flux'].abs().sum(),\n",
    "        'CH4':   pf['ch4_flux'].abs().sum() * gtp_100['ch4'],\n",
    "        'CFC-12': pf['cfc-12_flux'].abs().sum() * gtp_100['cfc-12'],\n",
    "        'total': pf['credits_gtp100'].sum()\n",
    "    },\n",
    "}).T\n",
    "\n",
    "print(gas_totals)"
   ]
  },
